OL,3,CRobin Swann pressed on 'playing
OL,4,Cpolitics' with health service
OL,6,FCommenting on the potential for pay
OL,7,Fuplifts to be jeopardised due to the
OL,8,Fconstraints of the health budget, Dr
OL,9,FGriffin added: "The levels of
OL,10,Fdiscontent among doctors about pay is
OL,11,Fnow so palpable that our consultant
OL,12,Fcolleagues plan to ballot members for
OL,13,Findustrial action, and a recent
OL,14,Findicative ballot of SAS (specialist
OL,15,Fdoctors) members returned a yes vote
OL,16,Ffor the same course of action.J"The
OL,17,Fhealth service cannot function without
OL,18,Fdoctors and they are leaving in
OL,19,Fgrowing numbers due to decreasing
OL,20,Fmorale from poor pay and high
OL,21,Fworkloads.J"We have been left with no
OL,22,Fchoice but to take action. If our
OL,23,Fgovernment wants the health service to
OL,24,Fsurvive and retain doctors, then it
OL,25,Fmust act now and prioritise staff pay.
